article.headline: Montana 100, Great Falls 52
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Raason Young scored 20 points to lead four Montana players in double figures in a 100-52 victory over Great Falls on Wednesday night. Young went 6 of 7 from 3-point range, where the Grizzlies (10-4) combined to shoot 13 of 21 (62 percent). Ryan Staudacher added 14 points and Michael Taylor 13 for Montana. The pair accounted for the other seven 3-pointers. Staudacher sank three 3-pointers in the opening four minutes to lead the Grizzlies out of the gate. They never trailed. Kevin Harris paced the NAIA-affiliated Argonauts (4-10) with 16 points. Montana had 29 points off 22 Great Falls turnovers and outrebounded the undersized Argos 34-24. Will Cherry added 11 points and seven assists for the Grizzlies.
